# Rust
/target/
**/*.rs.bk
# Cargo.lock is committed: the workspace ships a bin (crates/fprintd), and distro packaging and
# hardware runs need the exact graph docs/known-issues.md's pins were reasoned about.

# Upstream references cloned for reading/measurement (populate via `mise run clone-ref`)
/reference/

# mise local overrides
/mise.local.toml
/.mise.local.toml

# Editor / OS
/.idea/
/.vscode/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Generated by the tools this repo runs: a mutation sweep (`mise run mutants`) and the CI
# compilation cache. Both are reproducible from the tree; neither is an input to anything.
/mutants.out/
/mutants.out.old/
/.sccache/

# What a fuzz campaign generates. `fuzz/` is its own workspace (see its Cargo.toml): the corpus and
# the findings are reproducible from the seeds and the targets, and what survives a campaign is the
# frozen counterexample under crates/*/tests/regressions/, not the corpus that found it.
/fuzz/target/
/fuzz/corpus/
/fuzz/artifacts/
/fuzz/coverage/
